text: The Desert  A Poem This is my first time writing anything like this so I do apologize if its bad The   by   room   My prison of emotions   Entering the room   My emotions loomed    Emptiness    Desperate    Hopelessness    My mind once a forest   Slowly turned to a desert   Trees to dunes   lush bushes to dry cacti   Happiness and Sadness   so different yet merged as one   The once plentiful trees of joy   now turned to dunes of despair The bottle of tequila in one corner   The small stick of death in another   They were my only escape   Helped my mind hallucinate   It created an oasis in that desert   An oasis of hopefulness   All superficial   An imitation of what others felt   Ultimately my organs whipped with the belt   I didn t care   Hoping the substances would work   Desiring they would slowly kill me As my loved ones slept in peace   I got drunk and high waiting for release   Walking the tightrope   Looking death right in the eyes   STOP    END THE PAIN    I pleaded   To change the wasteland   To nothing   Asking him for a bullet to the brain   or a bloody knife to end the pain This was my first time writing something like this but if you are suffering from depression or suicidal thoughts writing is a great and healthy release mechanism  I do apologize if this poem kinda sucks but this is just how i feel and if anyone has any tips or criticisms about the poem please DM cause i really want to fine tune this poem  as it keeps me distracted from my depression
summary: The Desert is a poem written by a depressed person. It's his first attempt at writing something like this and he wants to fine tune it as it keeps him distracted from his depression. If you are suffering from depression or suicidal thoughts, writing is a good release mechanism.
